F\u00fcr ein Programm, das einem bestimmten Zweck dient und als Paket von einem Hersteller verkauft wird, siehe \"Anwendung\"."}

{"id": "303a4fbe-1c6e-4b46-8ebc-f8646c611091", "value": "Computer system programs, procedures, and associated documentation concerned with the operation of data processing systems, and which require hardware for use to be made of them. For individual collections or sequences of code provided by a user to perform a particular task, use \"programs.\" For programs that serve a particular purpose and that may be packaged and sold by a manufacturer use \"applications.\""}
{"id": "21dca980-d00c-424d-ad17-7c32d088c266", "value": "Names for people, places, or things that are commonly used, but not necessarily the official version of the name."}

{"id": "2e8c6638-cb1d-47bb-ab27-06f6ec2760b7", "value": "Refers to the process or branch of fine art concerned with creating sculpture, which are three-dimensional works. It refers particularly to carving or engraving a hard material, or with molding or casting a malleable material, so as to produce designs or figures in relief, in intaglio, or in the round. It is typically used to refer to the production of large or medium-sized objects in stone, clay, or bronze. The production of small objects in bronze or stone is typically referred to by a specific term, such as \"stone carving\" or \"die sinking.\" The production of sculpture in wood or ivory is typically referred to as \"carving,\" even though the finished work in these materials may be called \"sculpture (visual work).\""}
{"id": "18b6927d-cd52-4709-81c6-40bc20761a76", "value": "Statement or account that describes the seller in an acquisition event, listing characteristic features, or significant details."}
{"id": "9ab6f886-6fd9-4a75-934d-3d82ee8aaf63", "value": "Arranging a series or system of classes in order according to a principle, concept, purpose, interest, or other established criteria."}

{"id": "8fd5db9c-b681-4530-9463-f99bf602bd9c", "value": "Names for people, places, or things that are the fullest version of the name. For personal names, includes the first name, one or more middle names, one or more family names and last names, suffixes, and honorfics."}
{"id": "6474b02c-81bc-470a-9bb7-6cd34247301a", "value": "Regarding personal names, assumed names used by authors rather than their real names."}
{"id": "e38ca71b-103b-4407-86d1-7ffdad3b4134", "value": "Regarding personal names, assumed names used by actors and other performers rather than their real names."}
{"id": "e9d239d3-90cb-49c1-9d8f-d7935a71bfbb", "value": "Regarding personal names, last names acquired by a person, usually a woman, through marriage; distinguished from \"maiden names.\""}
{"id": "8248f95f-f977-4d37-8403-e67d831fc875", "value": "Regarding personal names, last names held by a woman prior to marriage, at which time she may adopt her husband's last name."}
{"id": "b75068d8-5887-48c2-a36c-c9e161a2a8ef", "value": "Names for people, places, or things that are legal or otherwise formally sanctioned."}

{"id": "0d0570bf-b727-4f40-985f-1749a951fbb1", "value": "The length of a straight horizontal line extending from one side to the other of a form. For the measure or distance of the extent across a surface, prefer \"breadth,\" although usage overlaps."}
{"id": "98486fdb-9f57-4ae8-9b45-c0f77fad1a7e", "value": "In general, the relative extent of something, its overall dimensions, magnitude, bulk, or bigness."}
{"id": "288dd2a4-08e5-4837-923f-a8abf5bdb1ae", "value": "The length of a straight vertical line extending from the bottom to the top of a form."}

{"id": "3a5055af-0a06-436a-ae2f-f2f523f37269", "value": "Identifying numbers assigned to a telephone or group of telephones; the numbers are dialled in order to make a connection to telephonic devices."}

{"id": "5b4d3f76-69e8-489c-b7f7-242f3e71c703", "value": "Sudden occurrences of violent expansion or bursting, intentional or accidental, caused by rapidly-developed internal energy, as by chemical or nuclear reaction, or esape of gases or vapors."}
{"id": "7c102cc3-892f-49cc-b05c-aaec308f413a", "value": "Titles that vary from the primary title. Distinguished from \"alternative titles.\""}

{"id": "785994bb-d1e6-40cc-a763-cf8acc1c864b", "value": "Generally, use of malleable material such as wax or clay to create a form which is three-dimensional. Specifically, in ceramic art, the shaping of an original ceramic object or the model or maquette from which a mold is made."}

{"id": "b0056271-5e19-4478-8788-3480c0db91cf", "value": "Geralmente, o uso de material male\u00e1vel como cera ou argila para criar uma forma que \u00e9 tridimensional. Especificamente, na arte da cer\u00e2mica, a modelagem de um objeto original de cer\u00e2mica ou o modelo ou maquete a partir do qual um molde \u00e9 feito."}
{"id": "69aa467e-5282-4528-8862-ef3199d68969", "value": "In computing, collections of related records stored in digital form for use by a computer and able to be processed by it."}
{"id": "dcd48ff9-e74b-4c7d-84d9-1e4aa673fc37", "value": "Listing items on hand."}

{"id": "62a19f15-fe13-4e62-9ed0-0c16f03d7906", "value": "Direitos exclusivos legalmente garantidos que determinam quem pode publicar, copiar ou distribuir uma obra de arte, escrita, m\u00fasica, fotografia ou outra obra. Obras protegidas por direitos autorais requerem a permiss\u00e3o do criador ou de outro detentor de direitos para seu uso. Algumas na\u00e7\u00f5es oferecem o uso justo, o que permite o uso limitado para fins educacionais. "}

{"id": "cda4897d-ada0-4bba-855e-235716c94bad", "value": "Exclusive, legally secured rights determining who may publish, copy, or distribute a work of art, writing, music, photograph, or other work. Works protected by copyright require the permission of the creator or other rights holder for their use. Some nations have the provision of fair use, which allows for limited use for educational purposes."}

{"id": "7aae5766-51a2-48b3-86a9-b1c48eb63f41", "value": "Rights concerning real and personal property, constitutionally protected in some nations; examples include the right to transfer, make contracts, conduct business, earn income through a property."}

{"id": "0f0f9349-a00e-4326-beba-8efceb3f5093", "value": "General term for the right or condition of complete dominion, title, or proprietary right to a real or other property as allowed by law. Ownership may be private, collective, or common. Ownership may be present even in the absence of possession."}
{"id": "ab56525b-702b-4988-98db-b830f6dc0610", "value": "The action of compressing something from its original shape in order to break, reduce, or destroy it."}
{"id": "ebdd829b-6800-4d71-a4c0-180204065d55", "value": "The legally recognized words or phrases under which a corporate body or institution is known and engages in action."}
{"id": "62746e3a-a176-45b3-9b3e-4b96cd943d0c", "value": "Producing visible forms primarily by delineation, usually by the direct application of material or instrument to the surface of the support."}

{"id": "21614b64-a9e6-47aa-bc48-6fdafd178954", "value": "Processo de produ\u00e7\u00e3o de formas vis\u00edveis principalmente por delineamento, geralmente pela aplica\u00e7\u00e3o direta de material ou instrumento \u00e0 superf\u00edcie do suporte."}

{"id": "7031a896-6149-4d9e-949e-7675739a49dc", "value": "The technique of applying a coat of opaque or semiopaque color to a painting with a nearly dry brush to make an image less defined or brilliant."}

{"id": "3adb7b25-9386-484e-93bf-6b8804a8ac43", "value": "The actions, functions, or event of issuing printed, taped, or otherwise reproduced records of knowledge or visual works in any medium for sale or distribution to the public."}

{"id": "fb738dc0-2a0a-46e4-8ab3-d73f09e4aa38", "value": "Multiple-word terms or names that are arranged in the form used in back-of-book indexing or other similar situations. Examples are Wren, Christopher and buttresses, flying. Distinguished from natural order terms or names."}

{"id": "9b4cc747-b06f-4a78-b43c-9c9e32195cbf", "value": "Refers to pictorial or photographic representations that faithfully (though not necessarily with total accuracy) depict actual locations. May be \"landscapes (representations),\" \"cityscapes (visual works),\" or \"townscapes (representations),\" though those terms tend to imply invention whereas \"topographical views\" implies recording of appearances. For faithful drawings of individual buildings, use \"measured drawings,\" \"record drawings,\" or \"as-built drawings.\""}
{"id": "86ce1455-b6e4-4f2a-9dc3-1e4b6ca043e7", "value": "The action or practice of observing, watching, or noticing."}

{"id": "8242c397-cb57-46e1-9238-83c71b8f73cb", "value": "The action or condition of causing an organization or group of people to cease to exist. Dissolution may involve official documents and usually occurs on a specific date. "}
{"id": "43e3c196-86fd-498f-a591-9010f57a6d47", "value": "A description including the title or name of the exhibition, its location, and other pertinent information."}

{"id": "c16760b2-eefd-4d19-ab24-c94023ae83c7", "value": "The process of shaping glass by blowing air through a blowpipe into a glob of molten glass and forming it with tongs and shears or by rolling it against a hard surface."}

{"id": "fbcc36ed-9687-44e9-a200-c08490c9cad4", "value": "Conducting an interpersonal exchange in order to obtain information from another for such purposes as for journalism, employment, publication, or research."}

{"id": "435f45b3-1010-4f85-852c-602a51406ffe", "value": "Refers to the action of physically destroying or deconstructing something; particularly aplied to a building or other structure that is pulled or knocked down, reduced to rubble or ruins."}
{"id": "305e4dcd-2472-4933-a483-0c2594153b07", "value": "A formal statement of the copyright or licensing of a work, and/or any restrictions placed on it. "}
{"id": "466c8922-5ebd-4540-9939-0f3f93e80bf6", "value": "Single distinct meaningful elements of speech or writing."}

{"id": "78292b98-47b0-4fc3-bf5e-b0013cb97888", "value": "The act of shaping, marking, or decorating wood, stone, or another material by cutting or incising, typically using tools such as chisels and other blades. It refers to this process as it is applied to small-scale objects or to objects that are not considered art. \"Carving\" may also be considered a sculpture technique that is employed in the creation of art."}
{"id": "fbb0c1ac-1ac4-4728-ab48-53c0659abcfa", "value": "Dissolution into separate parts, losing intactness or solidness."}

{"id": "f763b451-a4b9-4541-9fa7-486fe193eb79", "value": "Beschriftung, mit der etwas markiert wird, insbesondere zur Dokumentation oder zum Gedenken. Bei einer Drucksache ist dies eine spezielle, in Buchstaben aufgedruckte Information, die f\u00fcr gew\u00f6hnlich nicht Teil eines gr\u00f6\u00dferen Textes ist. Bez\u00fcglich antiker Texte werden damit die meisten erhaltenen schriftlichen \u00c4u\u00dferungen jeder L\u00e4nge, au\u00dfer Papyri, bezeichnet. F\u00fcr standardisierte Symbole oder Bezeichnungen auf Objekten, die wichtige Informationen enthalten, siehe \"Zeichen (Symbol)\"."}

{"id": "536e50aa-ade0-4c02-bd47-942ff7f0520e", "value": "Words, texts, lettering, or symbols marked on a work, including texts, legends, documentation notes, or commemoration. For standardized symbols or notations on objects that convey official information, use \"marks (symbols).\""}

{"id": "ddff7394-12f2-4a80-bb6c-6e1e3a2b2e00", "value": "An indication of the substances or materials used in the creation of a work, as well as any implements, production or manufacturing techniques, processes, or methods incorporated in its fabrication, presented in a syntax suitable for display to the end-user and including any necessary indications of uncertainty, ambiguity, and nuance. For works on paper, descriptions of watermarks may also be included."}

{"id": "8cb6ae25-fd96-4e68-8326-bfdf4f27ac55", "value": "A group of World Wide Web pages usually associated with a particular subject and connected via hyperlinks, made available online by an institution, company, government, or other organization."}

{"id": "28e7753e-5dac-481e-a855-fa74717633ed", "value": "Titles in fielded data that are formatted to sort in a particular way for display in a list or group, usually alphabetically, by the first word after an article, ie: \"title, the\"."}

{"id": "35320351-e46c-44fc-92b4-0f3dca1f5a7d", "value": "Sch\u00f6pferisches Werk, das den Ozean oder andere gro\u00dfe Gew\u00e4sser darstellt, in der das Wasser selbst die Szene beherrscht. Wenn kleinere Gew\u00e4sser dargestellt sind, ist \"Landschaft (Darstellung)\" zu verwenden. Wenn Schiffe, Schiffbau oder H\u00e4fen dargestellt sind, ist \"Marinemalerei (Visuelles Werk)\" zu verwenden."}

{"id": "c54f91ba-c39b-4a1a-a8c9-d61c8b2b427a", "value": "Creative works that depict the ocean or other large body of water where the water itself dominates the scene. When lesser bodies of water are depicted, use \"landscapes (representations).\" When ships, shipbuilding, or harbors are depicted, use \"marines (visual works).\""}

{"id": "986d1d10-0c3a-47fe-9ee2-78cd6290ad9e", "value": "Visual works or parts of works, in any medium, having subject matter that provides a visual representation of a story. Stories may be based on literary works, myths and religion, historical events, or any story. "}
{"id": "3763182c-5b6f-416e-9a3f-5f3fa127f39a", "value": "Application of paint in thick, opaque masses, usually with a well-loaded brush or a palette knife."}
{"id": "a3cb1105-f738-4cbb-a21c-aac9a55ee7b7", "value": "Series of words in connected speech or writing, forming the grammatically complete expression of a single thought."}
{"id": "f6771fad-ff93-4f3a-8799-ac7330bcb2d8", "value": "Painting technique in which paint is applied to a wet ground or onto wet paint."}

{"id": "c86109bf-a4d1-457b-b271-7f90cbb751d4", "value": "The affixing of a label to something in a collection or store of merchandise. For example, in the context of preparing objects for display, the affixing to or display near an object of a card or label that describes the object to viewers."}
{"id": "147d9235-4f0a-40c0-b81f-c9be06fae4a2", "value": "The activity of cutting with a quick and heavy blow with a hewing, hacking instrument, such as an ax, cleaver, sword, or the like."}

{"id": "98988656-fe14-4ca7-b890-ee3c6ee001df", "value": "A prose description of the salient characteristics of a work in relation to a particular style, historical period, group, school, or movement."}
